I'm running at almost full vac advance at idle off the
carb vac port, which is ported vacuum if the throttle
valve is completely closed, which it never is. 

For the purposes of vacuum advance, 
Ported vacuum is supposed to be at almost zero at idle
(butterfly closed). The idle speed adjustment screw on
most carbs opens the butterfly valve to bring the idle
up. Are there carbs that idle with the throttle
totally closed? 
I know the 32/36 DFEV sure as hell doesn't. 

