Is a dual vac can (Like on a stock 74 bus dizzy)
designed so that one side of it will require less
pressure to actuate if the other port is open and
vise/versa? 
Will the advance side of my dual can ignore minimal
vacuum (idle with the speed screw holding the valve
open)if the retard side of the can is plugged? 
I plan to port the manifold and hook it to the retard
port to try and balance it, but will plugging it help
for now?


